    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Simsia amplexicaulis are inflammation, fever reduction, and gastroenteritis. Simsia amplexicaulis has been used to treat infectious diarrhea and skin irritation, as it contains flavonoids and terpenoids that exhibit anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. Additionally, this plant has been used to treat malaria, cough, rheumatism, hypertension, dysentery, digestive issues, diabetes, and vomiting, due to its ability to reduce fever and alleviate symptoms. Simsia amplexicaulis has also been used to treat respiratory issues, fungal infections, gastrointestinal issues, wounds, and wound healing, as it stimulates collagen synthesis and promotes tissue repair. Furthermore, it has been used to treat skin infections and asthma, due to its antimicrobial and anti-inflammatory properties.",
