    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Simsia amplexicaulis are flavonoids which include kaempferol and quercetin that have antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, phenolic acids like ferulic acid that exhibit antimicrobial and antiproliferative activities, triterpenoids such as ursolic acid that display anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects, saponins which demonstrate anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial activities, and glycosides including iridoid glycosides that show hepatoprotective and anti-inflammatory properties. These bioactive compounds contribute to the plant's therapeutic potential in treating various health conditions. The antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities of these constituents are believed to be responsible for the plant's analgesic and anti-inflammatory effects. The antimicrobial properties of phenolic acids and saponins may also contribute to the plant's wound-healing and antiseptic activities. Furthermore, the immunomodulatory effects of ursolic acid and the hepatoprotective properties of iridoid glycosides suggest potential therapeutic applications in modulating the immune system and protecting liver function.",
